{#- Agent Workbench — /admin login (Phase A auth). Same tokens as the dashboard; fully
    offline (vendored css, no external refs). The form POSTs the per-process CSRF token plus
    the password; on success a session cookie (HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict) unlocks /admin.
    UI copy via the i18n catalog (`t`) — VI by default, EN via the switcher; the `error` is a
    localized server message from admin.py.

    Two states:
      * no_password (INERT) — no admin password configured. Login is impossible; the card shows
        how to BOOTSTRAP one (set the env var + restart). It deliberately renders NO password
        field (a setup form would let any local actor seize admin before the owner does — guarded
        by test_C1_no_password_login_page_shows_bootstrap_notice_not_a_setup_form).
      * password set — the real login form, plus secondary links (back to the read-only
        dashboard, how to change the password) and an owner-only "forgot password" recovery
        disclosure. There is NO web reset button by design: recovery requires filesystem access
        (delete .ops/admin.hash or set the env var), which is what proves you are the owner. -#}
<!doctype html>
<html lang="{{ lang }}">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>{{ t.login_meta_title }}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ url_for('static', filename='dashboard.css') }}">
</head>
<body>
<div class="auth-wrap">
  <main class="auth">
    <div class="auth__mark">
      <svg class="auth__logo" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M12 2.5 20.5 7v10L12 21.5 3.5 17V7L12 2.5Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        <path d="M12 8v5m0 3h.01" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
      </svg>
      <div>
        <div class="panel__eyebrow">{{ t.admin_eyebrow }}</div>
        <h1 class="auth__title">{% if no_password %}{{ t.login_title_no_password }}{% else %}{{ t.login_title }}{% endif %}</h1>
      </div>
      {% include "_lang_switch.html.jinja" %}
    </div>

    {% if no_password %}
    {#- INERT: no password configured. /admin is mounted but every action is refused and login
        is impossible. Show how to enable admin — NOT an in-page setup form (that would let any
        local actor seize admin before the owner does). -#}
    <p class="auth__lead">{{ t.login_inert_lead|safe }}</p>

    <div class="banner banner--danger" role="note">
      <span class="banner__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="banner__txt">{{ t.login_inert_banner|safe }}</span>
    </div>

    <div class="auth__field">
      <span class="auth__label">{{ t.login_inert_example_label }}</span>
      <p class="mono" style="word-break:break-all;font-size:.85em;margin:0">{{ t.login_inert_example_cmd }}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="auth__foot">
      <div class="auth__links">
        <a class="auth__link" href="/">{{ t.login_back_readonly }}</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    {% else %}
    <p class="auth__lead">{{ t.login_lead }}</p>

    {% if error %}
    <div class="banner banner--danger" role="alert">
      <span class="banner__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="banner__txt">{{ error }}</span>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <form method="post" action="/admin/login">
      <input type="hidden" name="csrf" value="{{ token }}">
      <div class="auth__field">
        <label class="auth__label" for="password">{{ t.login_password_label }}</label>
        <input id="password" name="password" type="password" class="auth__input"
               autocomplete="current-password" autofocus required>
      </div>
      <button class="btn btn--primary btn--block" type="submit">{{ t.login_btn }}</button>
    </form>

    <div class="auth__foot">
      <div class="auth__links">
        <a class="auth__link" href="/">{{ t.login_back_readonly2 }}</a>
        <span class="auth__link" style="border:0;cursor:default">{{ t.login_change_pw_hint|safe }}</span>
      </div>

      <details class="auth__recover">
        <summary>{{ t.login_forgot_summary }}</summary>
        <div class="auth__recover-body">
          <p>{{ t.login_forgot_p1|safe }}</p>
          <p style="margin:.5rem 0 0">{{ t.login_forgot_p2|safe }}</p>
          <p style="margin:.5rem 0 0">{{ t.login_forgot_p3|safe }}</p>
          <p style="margin:.5rem 0 0">{{ t.login_forgot_p4|safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <p class="auth__note">{{ t.login_note }}</p>
    {% endif %}
  </main>
</div>
</body>
</html>
